---
title: Provencal Pork Steak with Creamy New Potatoes, Leeky Green Beans and Hazelnuts
description: For a recipe that delivers on flavour and speed, this simple but delicious dish comes out on top. As one of Chef André’s creations, it’s no surprise to see his French heritage coming through by way of the provençale herbs in the pork marinade, giving this dish a certain je ne sais quoi. Served alongside balsamic greens and a creamy new potato salad, this is the perfect thing to bring a spark back to the dinner table.
